    <p>GENEVA • The World Health Or­gan­i­sa­tion (WHO) yes­ter­day in­sisted that there was still hope of con­quer­ing the coro­n­avirus pan­demic de­spite the pain and suf­fer­ing be­hind the loom­ing 750,000 death toll and 20 mil­lion cases.</p>
    <p>With both land­marks ex­pected to be reached within days, the WHO said it was never too late to take ac­tion to sup­press the Covid-19 cri­sis that has gripped the planet.</p>
    <p>“This week we will reach 20 mil­lion reg­is­tered cases of Covid-19 and 750,000 deaths,” WHO chief Te­dros Ad­hanom Ghe­breye­sus told a vir­tual press con­fer­ence.</p>
